%matplotlib inline

import os
import logging

from osgeo import gdal
import pygeoprocessing

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

plt.style.use('bmh')

import pandas as pd

dem_loc='dem_90m_pnnl-2.tif'
veg_loc='binary_veg_90m.tif'

dem = gdal.Open(dem_loc)
veg = gdal.Open(veg_loc)

dem_map=dem.ReadAsArray()
veg_map=veg.ReadAsArray()

OUTPUT_DIR = './output/'
if not os.path.exists(OUTPUT_DIR):
    os.makedirs(OUTPUT_DIR);

slope_raster = os.path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, 'slope.tif')

pygeoprocessing.calculate_slope(
    dem_dataset_uri='dem_90m_pnnl-2.tif',
    slope_uri=slope_raster)

swe_loc='ASO_swe_day7.tif'
swe = gdal.Open(swe_loc)

swe_map=swe.ReadAsArray()

plt.imshow(swe_map)
plt.colorbar()

def _create_mask(swe_range, dem_range, slope_range, veg):
    #_create_mask(swe_range,elevation_range,slope_range,forest_or_nonforest)

    # All blocks will be the same dimensions
    # Create a mask of invalid pixels due to nodata values
    swe_nodata = pygeoprocessing.get_nodata_from_uri(swe_loc)
    dem_nodata = pygeoprocessing.get_nodata_from_uri(dem_loc)
    slope_nodata = pygeoprocessing.get_nodata_from_uri(slope_raster)
    
    
    valid_mask = ((swe_map != swe_nodata) &
              (dem_map != dem_nodata) &
              (slope_map != slope_nodata))
 
    matching_pixels = (((swe_map[valid_mask]> np.min(swe_range)) & (swe_map[valid_mask] < np.max(swe_range))) &
                           ((dem_map[valid_mask]> np.min(dem_range))& (dem_map[valid_mask] < np.max(dem_range))) &
                           ((slope_map[valid_mask]> np.min(slope_range)) & (slope_map[valid_mask] < np.max(slope_range))) & 
                           (veg_map[valid_mask] == veg)) 
  
    out_nodata = -9999
    out_block = np.zeros((swe.RasterYSize,swe.RasterXSize))
    out_block[~valid_mask] = out_nodata
    out_block[valid_mask] =  matching_pixels 
    return out_block

mask1 = _create_mask([0.1,1], [3000,4000], [0,500], 1)
#_create_mask(swe_range,elevation_range,slope_range,forest_or_nonforest)
